{
  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix GitHub Pages Deployment Asset Loading Errors\n\nResolve 404 errors preventing static assets from loading correctly after deployment to GitHub Pages.\n\nRequirements:\n- Investigate and fix the base path configuration for GitHub Pages deployment (likely missing repository name in paths)\n- Ensure all asset references use correct paths relative to the deployment URL\n- Fix the following failing resources:\n  - hero-bg.svg (background image)\n  - /images/favicon.svg and /favicon.svg (favicon icons)\n  - about-preview.jpg (image in /images/ directory)\n  - site.webmanifest (PWA manifest file)\n- Update build configuration to handle GitHub Pages subdirectory deployment if applicable\n- Verify asset file locations in the deployed build output match referenced paths\n- Test all asset loading after deployment to confirm 404s are resolved\n- Ensure both root-level assets (favicon, manifest) and nested assets (/images/*) load correctly\n\nEdge cases to consider:\n- Project may be deployed to username.github.io/repo-name requiring base path prefix\n- Assets may exist but have incorrect casing in paths (case-sensitive on GitHub Pages)\n- Build process may not be copying all assets to the output directory\n- HTML meta tags and manifest references may need path adjustments",
